    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
               
	<pb facs="liv_001756_0001" n="0001"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><add place="inspace" rend="small brown"><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><hi rend="underline">Enclosure <choice><abbr>No</abbr><expan>Number</expan></choice> 2 in <choice><abbr>No</abbr><expan>Number</expan></choice> 96 of <date when="1862">1862</date></hi> <space extent="1" unit="chars"/><gap extent="2" unit="chars"/><date when="1862-03">March</date></add></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="2" unit="words"/><placeName><geogName type="harbor">Kongone Harbour</geogName></placeName> <date when="1862-03-19">19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> <del hand="#U2">May</del>
<lb/><space extent="6" unit="words"/>1862.</date></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><add place="marginleft" hand="#U1" rend="gray"><choice><abbr>req<hi rend="sup">d</hi></abbr><expan>required</expan></choice></add> <space extent="2" unit="chars"/><figure><figDesc>Calculation[?] initialed B.I.[?]</figDesc></figure> <space extent="1" unit="chars"/><add place="inspace" rend="brown small" hand="#U2"><choice><abbr>Rec<hi rend="sup">d</hi></abbr><expan>Received</expan></choice> <date when="1862-03-25">25 April 1862</date> per Gorgon</add></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><term type="occupation">Admiral</term> <space extent="4" unit="words"/><add hand="#U2"><hi rend="underline small brown">A.E. 315.</hi></add></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="2" unit="words"/><persName>Sir Baldwin Walker</persName></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="2" unit="words"/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/><add hand="#U1" rend="gray">âˆš</add> Sir</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="4" unit="words"/>I have ventured
<lb/>to send <persName>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Meller</persName> who has been
<lb/>suffering for some time from
<lb/><term type="ailment">remittent fever</term> and <term type="ailment">enlarged
<lb/>spleen</term> to the <placeName><region>Cape</region></placeName> for change
<lb/>of air as recommended by
<lb/><persName>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Kirk</persName> and <persName>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Ramsay</persName>,
<lb/>and I hope it may be in
<lb/>your power to afford him
<lb/>the benefits of the <placeName>hospital
<lb/>for <term type="occupation">naval officers</term></placeName>, for
<lb/>he well deserves any
<lb/>kindness that can be
<lb/><add place="marginleft" hand="#U3"><gap extent="2" unit="chars"/></add>bestowed - He is an excellent

    <pb facs="liv_001756_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>hardworking and amiable
<lb/>man, and an invaluable
<lb/>member of the <orgName>Expedition</orgName>.</p>
<lb/><p><persName>Captain Wilson</persName> having 
<lb/>provisioned us for three
<lb/>months, and <persName>Captain Oldfield</persName>
<lb/>having promised to arrange
<lb/>that a vessel should call on
<lb/>the <date when="1862-05-20">20<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> May</date> next with a crew
<lb/>of <orgName><placeName><geogName type="island">Johanna</geogName></placeName> men</orgName>, I forego
<lb/>the intention of proceeding to
<lb/><placeName><geogName type="island">Johanna</geogName></placeName> for supplies, in the
<lb/>hope that the vessel which
<lb/>may call will be able to
<lb/>spare us as much as we
<lb/>shall need for six months.
<lb/>We shall endeavour to be
<lb/>here from <date when="1862-05-20">20<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> May</date> to <date when="1862-06-01">1<hi rend="sup underline">st</hi> of
<lb/>June</date> - <space extent="1" unit="chars"/>The shell of the steamer
<lb/>for <placeName><geogName type="lake">Lake <choice><orig>Nyassa</orig><reg>Nyasa</reg></choice></geogName></placeName> will
<lb/>be then screwed together at
<lb/><placeName><settlement type="village">Shupanga</settlement></placeName>, and in the event
<lb/>of having provisions we
<lb/>shall go up to the cataracts
<lb/>and there remain till next
    
    <pb facs="liv_001756_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>year - <space extent="1" unit="chars"/>I am anxious not to
<lb/>return till we have the steamer
<lb/>fairly on the Lake and taken a<!-- geog: Nyassa -->
<lb/>trip in her.</p>
<lb/><p>In the event of your sending
<lb/>any merchant ship with coals
<lb/>or provisions for the station
<lb/>to arrive opposite this before
<lb/><date when="1862-05">May</date>, it would be a great
<lb/>service to us if you could
<lb/>ship ten good <term type="animal">draught oxen</term>, two
<lb/><term type="animal_foodstuff">cows</term> and a <orgName>Hottentot</orgName> <term type="occupation">driver</term>.
<lb/>The <term type="animal">mules</term> will carry all the 
<lb/>light gear and provisions, 
<lb/>and there being no <term type="insect">tsetse</term> <term type="animal_foodstuff">oxen</term>
<lb/>would do the rest - I have
<lb/>written to <persName><term type="occupation">General</term> Wynyard</persName> 
<lb/>the <term type="occupation">acting Governor</term> about the
<lb/>purchase of what we want
<lb/>but I beg you to remember
<lb/>that I do not contemplate animals
<lb/>coming by men of war - I refer
<lb/>only to a merchant vessel
<lb/>being freighted, and should that
<lb/>not occur soon the <term type="animal_foodstuff">oxen</term> &amp;
<lb/><term type="occupation">driver</term> might be left in charge
<lb/>of the <term type="nationality">Portuguese</term> <term type="occupation">officer</term> at this
<lb/>port, at any future time.</p>
                
    <pb facs="liv_001756_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/><p>The provisions I have <choice><orig>recieved</orig><reg>received</reg></choice> 
<lb/>from <persName><term type="occupation">Captain</term> Wilson</persName> and the
<lb/>prospect of more by the 
<lb/>arrangements of <persName><term type="occupation">Captain</term> Oldfield</persName>
<lb/>for <date when="1862-05"><choice><sic>may</sic><corr>May</corr></choice></date> next, will render the
<lb/>freighting of vessel from <placeName><region>Natal</region></placeName>
<lb/>specially for us unnecessary.</p>
<lb/><p>I beg leave to add to the "demand"
<lb/>contained in another letter.</p> 
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">spare gear for the boat, and 
<lb/>materials for repairing boats.</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><term type="plant">Hemp</term> for <term type="occupation">Engineer</term></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">20 or 30 feet of bulk's head</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">angle iron</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">1 or 2 iron plates <choice><orig><hi rend="small">3/16</hi></orig><reg>3/16</reg></choice> thick</p>
<lb/>
<lb/>
<lb/>
<lb/><p>I have the honour to be
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="words"/>your most obedient servant
<lb/><space extent="3" unit="words"/><persName>David Livingstone</persName></p> 
    
            </div>
